request.description:
This endpoint makes an HTTP GET request to retrieve the first page of course data.

### Response

The response will be in JSON format with the following schema:

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "totalItems": {
            "type": "integer"
        },
        "items": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
                "type": "object",
                "properties": {
                    "id": {
                        "type": "integer"
                    },
                    "name": {
                        "type": "string"
                    },
                    "description": {
                        "type": "string"
                    },
                    "code": {
                        "type": "string"
                    },
                    "startDate": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "format": "date-time"
                    },
                    "endDate": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "format": "date-time"
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

 ```

### Update Course Name

This endpoint allows the client to update the name of a specific course.

#### Request

- Method: PUT

- URL: `https://localhost:51039/course/21/name?newName=Spencer`


#### Response

The response is in JSON format and has the following schema:

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "id": {
            "type": "integer"
        },
        "name": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "description": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "code": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "startDate": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "endDate": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "enrolledStudents": {
            "type": "array"
        },
        "events": {
            "type": "array"
        }
    }
}

 ```

### GET /event/page/1

This endpoint retrieves a paginated list of events.

#### Request

No request body is required for this endpoint.

- Path Parameters

    - page (number, required): The page number to retrieve.


#### Response

The response will be in JSON format with the following schema:

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "totalItems": {
            "type": "number"
        },
        "items": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
                "type": "object",
                "properties": {
                    "id": {
                        "type": "number"
                    },
                    "name": {
                        "type": "string"
                    },
                    "description": {
                        "type": "string"
                    },
                    "code": {
                        "type": ["string", "null"]
                    },
                    "startDate": {
                        "type": "string"
                    },
                    "endDate": {
                        "type": "string"
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

 ```

### GET /student/page/1

This endpoint retrieves a page of student data.

#### Request

No request body is required for this endpoint.

#### Response

The response is in JSON format and follows the schema below:

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "totalItems": {
            "type": "number"
        },
        "items": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
                "type": "object",
                "properties": {
                    "id": {
                        "type": "number"
                    },
                    "name": {
                        "type": "string"
                    },
                    "email": {
                        "type": "string"
                    },
                    "address": {
                        "type": "string"
                    },
                    "phoneNumber": {
                        "type": "string"
                    },
                    "enrollmentDate": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "format": "date-time"
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

 ```

The endpoint retrieves information about a specific student identified by their ID. The response returns a JSON object with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "id": {
      "type": "integer"
    },
    "name": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "email": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "address": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "phoneNumber": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "enrollmentDate": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "enrolledCourses": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "id": {
            "type": "integer"
          },
          "name": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "description": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "code": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "startDate": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "endDate": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```
